  "texts": [
    "Other uses of GANs could be to enhance fossil imagery by reconstructing incomplete specimens, thereby providing more insights into the fine details of fossils.",
    "GANs also possess the capability to replicate and adapt artistic styles, which can be extended to paleontological data (Yi et al. 2019).",
    "Consequently, GANs could facilitate the generation of detailed fossil images from incomplete or deteriorated data, thereby broadening research and educational prospects in paleontology while utilizing corrupted/incomplete datasets.",
    "Enhancing fossil images is a critical task in paleontology, aimed at addressing issues such as image noise, insufficient feature differentiation, artifacts from imaging devices arising from limitations in imaging technologies, the state of fossil preservation, and the methodologies employed during initial data archiving.",
    "Consequently, a significant portion of the datasets necessitate advanced preprocessing to render them suitable for analytical applications."
